    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all thirteen credibility factors. Seven factors were formally assessed; six were flagged as not-assessed epistemic gaps. Despite multiple achieved levels falling below required levels, the assessment package is accepted for submission, with open gaps documented for regulatory follow-up. Monte Carlo UQ results demonstrate the 95th-percentile NIH prediction remains below the clinical threshold. The mesh convergence study (GCI 3.7%) provides confidence in discretization adequacy at the design point.",
